<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-23T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-23T15:00:00-05:00" n="1539" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1539">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/64a.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Vice Consul <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>.</hi><note n="143" xml:id="d1539fn143">Same
                                    telegram to Special Agent Carothers.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-23T15:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 23, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Christian Brothers, who report two of their number killed at
                                Zacatecas and eleven imprisoned, have schools at Saltillo,
                                Acalzinco, Mexico, Mixcoac, Morelia, Puebla, Queretaro and Toluca.
                                Please bring these schools to the attention of Carranza and urge him
                                to give instructions to local authorities to prevent injury to
                                persons or property.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>